xen-virgl-install README

-------------Intalling-----------------------------------------------------
tested on Ubuntu 16.04

run ./install
-will prompt for sudo password
-the vm will boot with the fedora iso the first time. Install fedora and reboot VM
-in VM run:
	-dnf copr enable kraxel/virgl
	-dnf update

what this script does:
-sets up network bridge for xen
-install dependicies
-set up file system xen,virgl,adn qemu in home directory. Will put xen-disks in root.
-Download xen from git
-install xen
-Download virglrender from git
-install virglrenderer
-download most recent qemu
-install/build qemu with SDL 2.0, openGL, GTK, and virGLrenderer enabled
-updates grub
-install xen-utils (4.6 version but it does the trick)
	-this updates grub and files system for various thing to make xen run smothly
-downloads and setups fedora 24 iso
-make .img disk image for VM
-makes script to run xen on start so xl works from boot

---------------Current known problems--------------------------------------------

PROBLEM: networking bridge isnt working
FIX:
	-if script was run multiple times check for and delete repeated text in the following:
                /etc/network/interfaces
                /etc/fstab

PROBLEM: sometimes the git clones can freeze up
FIX:
	-wait longer....
	IF STILL BROKEN
	-comment out git clones for xen,virglrenderer,qemu
	-manually git clone these into home directory
	-if git freezes again crtl-c and retry
        -when all folders have been cloned re-run script with git commented out
	-depending how far script got you might want to delete the repeated text in:
		/etc/network/interfaces
		/etc/fstab
 
PROBLEM:if username isnt "user" the qemu path in the cfg wil need to be changed
FIX:
	-manually go into /etc/xen/gfedora.cfg
	-change: device_model_override = "/home/user/qemu-2.6.0/x86_64-softmmu/qemu-system-x86_64"
	-to: device_model_override = "/home/<username>/qemu-2.6.0/x86_64-softmmu/qemu-system-x86_64"

